<POST>
<POSTER> Mike Williams </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2005-08-26T11:01:00 </POSTDATE>

The thing that's causing your template layout to break is the fact that
you're now using a strict DOCTYPE.

If you take your existing index page, with no Google API on it at all,
and just change the DOCTYPE from its current HTML 4.01 Transitional
doctype to XHTML 1.0 Strict, then you'll find that the layout alignment
has been broken.

You either need to rewrite your template in accordance with XHTML 1.0,
or put back the HTML 4.01 doctype and hope that the Google map doesn't
break too badly. From what I've seen other on other people's pages, the
Google stuff seems to look OK with the HTML 4.01 doctype, but the
documentation says that the XHTML doctype makes &quot;layout and behaviors
much more predictable across browsers&quot;.

</POST>



